\begin_layout Standard
This paper presents an energy management management system on solar panels
 which are in the EST / UEA.
 In this systems are very important for that harness solar PV.
 For it draws up a management program that addresses the monitoring functions,
 data collection, supervision and control of the energy generated.
 The screens created for the system can look up from the network using TCP
 / IP protocol.
 The manager is intelligent qualities, using the technique of fuzzy logic.
 For this describes the existing process our case the interface to adequacy
 of supervision and measurement function manager with Arduino, Simulink
 PLC and Mitsubishi.
 Chapter 3 presents a software developed for monitoring solar radiation
 and room temperature to study the effects of climate influence on the productio
n of electricity by photovoltaic solar panels.
 Experimental results are presented to illustrate the behavior of the electricit
y production in photovoltaic solar system.
\end_layout

